    <item>
      <title>Best Fast-Charging Power Stations Under $1000 for Van Life (700Wh&#43;)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/best-of/best-fast-charging-power-stations-under-1000/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/best-of/best-fast-charging-power-stations-under-1000/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Fast charging is how you &lt;strong&gt;recover&lt;/strong&gt; when van life gets real: heat, clouds, humid nights, quiet hours, workdays, and missed solar.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;CAVL rules for this page:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;700Wh+ minimum&lt;/strong&gt; (non-negotiable)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;rank and frame decisions by &lt;strong&gt;time-to-recover&lt;/strong&gt; over raw storage&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;price-drift safe&lt;/strong&gt; structure (no “this is always under $1000” promises)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you want the fully sourced deep-dive buyer page (manufacturer claims + third-party tests), start here:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Starter Tier Survival Plan: Stay Stable on an Under-$500 Power Setup (700Wh&#43;)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/starter-tier-survival-plan/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/starter-tier-survival-plan/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The starter tier can work in van life—but only if you run it like a system.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page is for people using an &lt;strong&gt;under-$500&lt;/strong&gt; style setup (CAVL floor still applies: &lt;strong&gt;700Wh+&lt;/strong&gt;) who want stability without constantly “needing more.”&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you’re not sure whether starter tier is enough for you, use:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Starter Tier vs Upgrade Tier: When Under $500 Is Enough (and When It Isn’t)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/starter-tier-vs-upgrade-tier/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/starter-tier-vs-upgrade-tier/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Budget questions are really stability questions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The under-$500 tier can absolutely work—&lt;strong&gt;if your routine supports it&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;The under-$1000 tier is usually about one thing: &lt;strong&gt;faster recovery windows&lt;/strong&gt; so you don’t spiral.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page helps you choose a tier without hype or regret.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Tier 2 Bad Week Protocol: Stay Stable on an Under-$1000 Setup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/tier-2-bad-week-protocol/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/tier-2-bad-week-protocol/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Bad weeks are when plans get exposed: heat, humidity, cloudy stretches, quiet hours, work pressure—sometimes all at once.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tier 2 (under-$1000) helps most when you use it &lt;strong&gt;early and intentionally&lt;/strong&gt;, not as a last-minute panic button.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Start here if you’re new to the ladder:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Under-$1000 Upgrade Plan: Use Fast Charging to Stay Stable (700Wh&#43;)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/under-1000-upgrade-plan/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 22 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/under-1000-upgrade-plan/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The under-$1000 tier isn’t about luxury. It’s about &lt;strong&gt;recovery windows&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;If you upgrade and still feel stressed, it’s usually because:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;you didn’t change the routine with the gear, or&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;fast charging became a panic button instead of a planned tool.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page shows how to use the under-$1000 tier the CAVL way: calm, recoverable, and routine-backed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
